<subSubSection id="C3136ACE7321FFAB91D4F88AF7D3F87D" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB639457321FFAB91D4F88AF7D3F87D" blockId="12.[192,1440,1866,1927]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577321FFAB91D4F88AF733F89E" bold="true" box="[192,324,1866,1892]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Etymology.</emphasis>
Latin, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67321FFAB9089F88AF788F89E" authorityName="Botero and Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[413,511,1866,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Temnopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiculata">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577321FFAB9089F88AF788F89E" box="[413,511,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">spiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
,” referring to the spicules of the basal antennomeres, distinctly longer than in other species in the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136ACE7320FFAA91D4FF16F434FD70" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB639457320FFAA91D4FF16F348FDBF" blockId="13.[192,1442,213,581]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA91D4FF16F758FF0A" bold="true" box="[192,303,214,240]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67320FFAA9022FF17F47EFF0A" authority="Botero &amp; Santos-Silva, 2022" authorityName="Botero &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[310,521,214,240]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Temnopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiculata" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA9022FF17F47EFF0A" box="[310,521,214,240]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Temnopis spiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA9305FF16F4EDFF15" bold="true" box="[529,666,213,240]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24E582C7320FFAA9305FF16F4EDFF15" box="[529,666,213,240]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67320FFAA9227FF17F208FF0A" authority="Martins, Galileo" authorityName="Martins, Galileo" box="[819,1151,214,240]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Temnopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubricollis">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA9227FF17F535FF0A" box="[819,834,215,240]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA9245FF16F5C8FF0A" box="[849,959,214,240]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">rubricollis</emphasis>
Martins, Galileo
</taxonomicName>
and Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009 (
<figureCitation id="133225C07320FFAA901CFF38F7F2FEE8" box="[264,389,248,274]" captionStart="Figures 23–32" captionStartId="11.[192,279,1765,1791]" captionTargetBox="[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 23–32. Temnopis spp. 23–28) T. spiculata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 23) Dorsal habitus;24) Ventral habitus; 25) Lateral habitus; 26) Antennomeres III–V; 27) Head, frontal view; 28) Prosternal process. 29–30) T. rubricollis Martins, Galileo and Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009, holotype male: 29) Dorsal habitus; 30) Ventral habitus. 31–32) T. fuscipennis Martins, 1978, male (MZSP 49216) from Brazil (Pará, Ulianópolis): 31) Dorsal habitus; 32) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533594/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 29–30</figureCitation>
), but differs as follows: distance between upper eye lobes 1.5 times width of one upper lobe; antennae longer, reaching elytral apex near apex of antennomere V; scape with spicules ventrally; spicules of the antennomeres III–V longer (
<figureCitation id="133225C07320FFAA9316FEFCF424FEAD" box="[514,595,316,343]" captionStart="Figures 23–32" captionStartId="11.[192,279,1765,1791]" captionTargetBox="[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 23–32. Temnopis spp. 23–28) T. spiculata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 23) Dorsal habitus;24) Ventral habitus; 25) Lateral habitus; 26) Antennomeres III–V; 27) Head, frontal view; 28) Prosternal process. 29–30) T. rubricollis Martins, Galileo and Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009, holotype male: 29) Dorsal habitus; 30) Ventral habitus. 31–32) T. fuscipennis Martins, 1978, male (MZSP 49216) from Brazil (Pará, Ulianópolis): 31) Dorsal habitus; 32) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533594/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); elytral pubescence more abundant (
<figureCitation id="133225C07320FFAA92ECFEFCF23FFEAC" box="[1016,1096,316,342]" captionStart="Figures 23–32" captionStartId="11.[192,279,1765,1791]" captionTargetBox="[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 23–32. Temnopis spp. 23–28) T. spiculata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 23) Dorsal habitus;24) Ventral habitus; 25) Lateral habitus; 26) Antennomeres III–V; 27) Head, frontal view; 28) Prosternal process. 29–30) T. rubricollis Martins, Galileo and Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009, holotype male: 29) Dorsal habitus; 30) Ventral habitus. 31–32) T. fuscipennis Martins, 1978, male (MZSP 49216) from Brazil (Pará, Ulianópolis): 31) Dorsal habitus; 32) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533594/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
); and prosternal process at the same level of the prosternum (
<figureCitation id="133225C07320FFAA9302FE9EF41FFE82" box="[534,616,350,376]" captionStart="Figures 23–32" captionStartId="11.[192,279,1765,1791]" captionTargetBox="[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 23–32. Temnopis spp. 23–28) T. spiculata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 23) Dorsal habitus;24) Ventral habitus; 25) Lateral habitus; 26) Antennomeres III–V; 27) Head, frontal view; 28) Prosternal process. 29–30) T. rubricollis Martins, Galileo and Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009, holotype male: 29) Dorsal habitus; 30) Ventral habitus. 31–32) T. fuscipennis Martins, 1978, male (MZSP 49216) from Brazil (Pará, Ulianópolis): 31) Dorsal habitus; 32) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533594/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67320FFAA938FFE9FF551FE82" box="[667,806,350,376]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Temnopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubricollis">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA938FFE9FF4DCFE82" box="[667,683,351,376]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA93ACFE9EF551FE82" box="[696,806,350,376]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">rubricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(male), the distance between upper eye lobes is equal to width of one upper lobe, antennae shorter, reaching the elytral apex at middle of antennomere VI, scape without spicules ventrally, spicules of the antennomeres III‒V shorter (
<figureCitation id="133225C07320FFAA92BDFE62F58DFE46" box="[937,1018,418,444]" captionStart="Figures 23–32" captionStartId="11.[192,279,1765,1791]" captionTargetBox="[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 23–32. Temnopis spp. 23–28) T. spiculata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 23) Dorsal habitus;24) Ventral habitus; 25) Lateral habitus; 26) Antennomeres III–V; 27) Head, frontal view; 28) Prosternal process. 29–30) T. rubricollis Martins, Galileo and Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009, holotype male: 29) Dorsal habitus; 30) Ventral habitus. 31–32) T. fuscipennis Martins, 1978, male (MZSP 49216) from Brazil (Pará, Ulianópolis): 31) Dorsal habitus; 32) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533594/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
), elytral pubescence sparser (
<figureCitation id="133225C07320FFAA9456FE62F3E4FE46" box="[1346,1427,418,444]" captionStart="Figures 23–32" captionStartId="11.[192,279,1765,1791]" captionTargetBox="[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 23–32. Temnopis spp. 23–28) T. spiculata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 23) Dorsal habitus;24) Ventral habitus; 25) Lateral habitus; 26) Antennomeres III–V; 27) Head, frontal view; 28) Prosternal process. 29–30) T. rubricollis Martins, Galileo and Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009, holotype male: 29) Dorsal habitus; 30) Ventral habitus. 31–32) T. fuscipennis Martins, 1978, male (MZSP 49216) from Brazil (Pará, Ulianópolis): 31) Dorsal habitus; 32) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533594/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
), and prosternal process at the same level of the prosternum only basally (
<figureCitation id="133225C07320FFAA92E6FE04F233FE24" box="[1010,1092,452,478]" captionStart="Figures 23–32" captionStartId="11.[192,279,1765,1791]" captionTargetBox="[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 23–32. Temnopis spp. 23–28) T. spiculata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 23) Dorsal habitus;24) Ventral habitus; 25) Lateral habitus; 26) Antennomeres III–V; 27) Head, frontal view; 28) Prosternal process. 29–30) T. rubricollis Martins, Galileo and Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009, holotype male: 29) Dorsal habitus; 30) Ventral habitus. 31–32) T. fuscipennis Martins, 1978, male (MZSP 49216) from Brazil (Pará, Ulianópolis): 31) Dorsal habitus; 32) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533594/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). It is also slightly similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67320FFAA949EFE05F7ACFDFA" authority="Martins, 1978" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Temnopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA949EFE05F3EDFE24" box="[1418,1434,453,478]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA91D4FE26F74EFDFA" box="[192,313,486,512]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">fuscipennis</emphasis>
Martins, 1978
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="133225C07320FFAA90FDFE26F428FDFA" box="[489,607,486,512]" captionStart="Figures 23–32" captionStartId="11.[192,279,1765,1791]" captionTargetBox="[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[294,1338,213,1736]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 23–32. Temnopis spp. 23–28) T. spiculata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 23) Dorsal habitus;24) Ventral habitus; 25) Lateral habitus; 26) Antennomeres III–V; 27) Head, frontal view; 28) Prosternal process. 29–30) T. rubricollis Martins, Galileo and Limeira-de-Oliveira, 2009, holotype male: 29) Dorsal habitus; 30) Ventral habitus. 31–32) T. fuscipennis Martins, 1978, male (MZSP 49216) from Brazil (Pará, Ulianópolis): 31) Dorsal habitus; 32) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533594/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 31‒32</figureCitation>
), but differs by the elytra unicolorous (bicolored in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67320FFAA958FFE27F346FDFA" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1978" box="[1179,1329,486,513]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Temnopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA958FFE27F2DBFDFA" box="[1179,1196,487,512]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA95ACFE26F346FDFA" box="[1208,1329,486,512]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), spicules of basal flagellomeres longer (shorter in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67320FFAA939EFDC9F557FDD8" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1978" box="[650,800,520,547]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Temnopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA939EFDC9F4EEFDD8" box="[650,665,521,546]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA93B3FDC8F557FDD8" box="[679,800,520,546]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), antennomere V not narrowed apically (narrowed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67320FFAA949EFDC9F74EFDBE" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Temnopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA949EFDC9F3EEFDD8" box="[1418,1433,521,546]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA91D4FDEAF74EFDBE" box="[192,313,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and distal antennomeres slightly lighter than basal ones (strongly lighter in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67320FFAA958CFDEBF359FDBE" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1978" box="[1176,1326,554,581]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Temnopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA958CFDEBF2DEFDBE" box="[1176,1193,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577320FFAA95A1FDEAF359FDBE" box="[1205,1326,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
